Package: causamed
Title: Mediation in the causal inference framework
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Antoine", "Baldassari", email = "baldassarian@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements mediation formulas from Tyler Vanderweele's 2015 book
    Regression methods for continuous mediator/outcome
    IPTW-based method for scenario with exposure-induced M->Y confounding
    G-estimation based method for joint effect of multiple mediators
    Calculation of random interventional analogues to direct and indirect effects
    Structural means models to deal with exposure-induced confounding of M->Y given a continuous exposure or mediator (section 5.3.5)
    Handling of mice objects to add to resampler (slow but more stable than pooling from few imputed datasets)
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.4)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Imports:
  dplyr,
  magrittr,
  nnet
